        public void scrub(int count)
        Reverses the stream 'count' tokens back, causing the tokens to be removed from the stream. Can be used to erase tokens which parser lookahead has summoned, but which represent input to be handled by an 'island grammar'.
        Parameters:
        count - The amount to scrub
